CauseRemedy.Cause: The actual mains voltage is too high.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Look for an allowed mains voltage.

DiagMessage.Description: One phase is failed by 3-phase-supply.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The mains voltage supply is faulty.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Analyze the mains voltage supply and resolve the problem.

CauseRemedy.Remedy: Activate a filter, which effects, that the phase monitoring waits longer, until this error is set.

CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the parameter Mains type and correct its value. Switch on again the mains voltage.

DiagMessage.MessageText: Mains voltage over brake resistor operating voltage
DiagMessage.Description: The mains voltage has voltage peaks that causes the brake chopper to be switched on.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Voltage peaks occur by the mains voltage.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Analize the mains supply and make, that the voltage peaks do not happen.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The parametrization of DC link max voltage (0x8000:01) is too low.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check your application and parametrize the DC link max voltage higher, if necessary. In this case the switchOn threshold voltage (0x9006:0C) of the brake chopper should has been changed.

DiagMessage.Description: The connected mains type (3Ph/AC, 1Ph/AC or DC) does not match with parameterized value of mains type (0x8000:04).

CauseRemedy.Cause: Mains type is parameterized with wrong value.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the parameter Mains type and correct its value.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The mains supply is not connected right.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the mains supply and connected it right, Switch on the mains voltage again.

CauseRemedy.Cause: An unknown software failure happened.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Switch off the mains voltage and the 24V-supply. Switch on them again. If this error happens repeatedly, please contact your Beckhoff office.

DiagMessage.Description: An error in the internal configuration has occurred.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The firmware update was not succesfully.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Switch off the mains voltage and the 24V-supply. Switch on them again and start a new firmware update. If this error happens repeatedly, please contact your Beckhoff office.

DiagMessage.Description: Default values of parameters could not be loaded.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Device ids or power board ids are missing in eeprom.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Switch off the mains voltage and the 24V-supply. Switch on them again. If this error happens repeatedly, please contact your Beckhoff office.

DiagMessage.Description: A parameterization error has occurred.
Brake chopper failured.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Brake chopper is damaged.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Switch off the mains voltage and the 24V-supply. Switch on them again. If this error happens repeatedly, please contact your Beckhoff office.

DiagMessage.Description: Your connected brake resistor (internal or external) was overloaded.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Current at connected brake resistor is too high. The brake resistor may be damaged.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Switch off the mains voltage and the 24V-supply. Check whether your brake resistor is damaged, if external one connected. Try to operate power supply module again. If this error happens repeatedly, please contact your Beckhoff office.

DiagMessage.Description: No connected brake resistor can be detected.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Internal brake resistor is faulty and any external brake resistor has not been connected.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Switch off the mains voltage and the 24V-supply. Switch on them again. If this error happens repeatedly, please contact your Beckhoff office.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The connection bridge for the internal brake resistor is missing and any external brake resistor has not been connected.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Plug in the connection bridge or connect an external brake resistor.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The connection bridge for the internal brake resistor is not pugged in, an external brake resistor has been connected but this may be damaged.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check your external brake resistor. If this is not damaged, try to operate the power supply module again. If this error happens repeatedly, please contact your Beckhoff office.

DiagMessage.MessageText: Brake resistor power overload by DC link overvoltage
DiagMessage.Description: Brake resistor was disabled because of power overload.
Device description file does not match to device or to firmware.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Wrong file by firmware update choosen.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Start again a firmware update with the right file.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Wrong file by device description update choosen.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Start again a firmware update with the right file. A separate device description update is not necessary because this is made automatically by a firmware update.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The firmware or device description files do not match to device.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the files. Change them or change the device, if necesary.
